Gates Says Transaction Tax Could Generate $50 Billion, FT Says

-- B y   C a r o l i n e   A l e x a n d e r
-- 
2011-09-24T09:04:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-24/gates-says-transaction-tax-could-generate-50-billion-ft-says.html
A tax on financial transactions
could generate $50 billion for development aid if applied across
the Group of 20 nations, Microsoft Corp. Chairman  Bill Gates 
said in draft report to the G20, the Financial Times  reported 
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Caroline Alexander in  London  at 
 calexander1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net . 